  "texts": [
    "The implementation leverages Python's ThreadPoolExecutor to enable parallel operation of search and analysis.",
    "For the former, multiple search queries can execute simultaneously within each subtask.",
    "When the search_agent node activates, it spawns multiple search threads by creating \"future\" tickets that are appended to a list of all open tickets (search_futures).",
    "The function \"future.result()\" in the penultimate line waits until all parallel tasks have been executed before delivering the results.",
    "# Perform parallel searches using ThreadPoolExecutor search_futures = [] for query in subtask ['search_queries ']: future = self. executor."
  ],
